<item>
            <title>[LU-8699] Further fsx improvements</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-8699</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;As per the discussions with Andreas, I am filing this bug.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;After &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-7129&quot; title=&quot;FSX with DIRECTIO support&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-7129&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-7129&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; is landed,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;merge the multi-fd support (-I) into the upstream fsx (in xfstests)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;look at the commit history of fsx.c to see what we&apos;ve changed since the original version, so that the various compiler/coverity fixes are not missed.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;check if O_DIRECT could be enabled on e.g. 1/2 of fds (or maybe some 1/N ratio that is optionally specified with the -Z option) to compete with buffered I/O on the same system.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Andreas, &lt;br/&gt;
please correct me if wrong OR&lt;br/&gt;
update, if I have missed anything. &lt;br/&gt;
Thanks.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
